<h2>Questions About Dryer Vent Installation Cost</h2>

<h3>How much does dryer vent installation cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
<p>$149–450 total depending on vent run length, number of bends, and whether we need to penetrate an exterior wall. A short straight run is $149–220. A longer run with bends or a new wall penetration is $320–450. We assess on-site and give you an exact quote before starting.</p>

<h3>How long does dryer vent installation take?</h3>
<p>Most installations take 1–3 hours depending on complexity. A simple short run through an existing exit takes about an hour. A longer run with wall penetration through stucco takes 2–3 hours. We give you a time estimate when we assess the job.</p>

<h3>Can I use flexible foil duct for my dryer vent?</h3>
<p>No — and we won't install it. California building code and LG's installation specifications both require rigid or semi-rigid metal duct. Flexible foil duct traps lint at every ridge, crushes and kinks easily, and is a fire hazard. If your current installation uses foil duct, we'll replace it with proper rigid metal.</p>

<h3>My LG dryer shows d80 or d90 — is it the vent installation?</h3>
<p>Very likely yes if the codes started appearing shortly after installation or if the vent has never been properly sized. d80 means 80% airflow restriction. We assess the vent system, identify whether it's a blockage or an installation problem, and fix it. See our <a href="/symptoms/lg-dryer-flow-sense-error/">LG dryer Flow Sense error page</a> for more detail.</p>

<h3>Do I need a permit for dryer vent installation in Los Angeles?</h3>
<p>For simple replacement of existing ductwork with the same routing, typically no permit is required. For new construction or significant rerouting that involves cutting through walls or ceilings, local permit requirements vary by city and HOA. We can advise on your specific situation when we assess the job.</p>

<h3>Can you come today?</h3>
<p>Yes — call (323) 990-7550. Same-day dryer vent installation and vent cleaning across Los Angeles County, Orange County, and Ventura County, typically 2–4 hours from your call.</p>

